  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Grate the <strong>mature</strong>&nbsp;<strong>cheddar&nbsp;</strong>finely</p>\r\n<p>Add a handful of <strong>flour</strong> to a plate</p>\r\n<p>Crack the <strong>egg<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into a shallow bowl and beat with a fork</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> to another plate and combine with the<strong> grated cheese</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Place your hand flat on the&nbsp;<strong>chicken breast<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Slice in half as if you were cutting a burger bun, so you are left with two thinner pieces of&nbsp;<strong>chicken</strong></p>\r\n<p>Coat the <strong>chicken </strong>in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off the excess, then add it into the<strong> beaten egg</strong> and finally press it firmly into the <strong>cheesy&nbsp;breadcrumbs</strong>&nbsp;to evenly coat all over</p>\r\n<p>Refrigerate until step 5&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\r\n<p>Once done, drain the <strong>linguine</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, re-boil a kettle<br /><br />Peel and finely slice the <strong>garlic&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Roll the <strong>lemon<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with your hand on a hard surface (to release more juice!) and cut in half</p>\r\n<p>Cut half the <strong>lemon</strong> into wedges and reserve for garnish</p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>chicken stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1141.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of<strong>&nbsp;vegetable oil</strong>&nbsp;over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the&nbsp;<strong>breaded chicken</strong>&nbsp;and cook for 4-5 min on each side or until golden and cooked through</p>\r\n<p>Tip: add more oil if your pan is looking a little dry&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, transfer the <strong>breaded chicken</strong> to kitchen paper (keep the pan!)</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
